Stiffed - Sex Sells (2003)

MP3 VBR



Review:

Stiffed's Santi White prances like Gwen Stefani and growls like Chrissie Hynde on her band's official debut release, Sex Sells. This EP is a brash mix of post-punk aesthetic and kitschy new wave bits, and Stiffed gives it to you good with a sucker punch. From the twitchy basslines of &quot;Everybody's Got It&quot; to the gnarling rock romp of &quot;He Looks Good,&quot; Stiffed struts with a quirky appeal. They're melodically raw on the punk-pop party of &quot;Yes,&quot; but &quot;What You Gon' Do&quot; highlights White's infectious stance as a frontwoman. She's raw, but unafraid to say what's on her mind. If that means she's disappointed with her boy toy of the moment, so be it. Sex Sells screams &quot;Girl Power!&quot; without stereotypical connotations floating in from both sides. It's pure rock &amp; roll and hell hath no fury like a woman scorned! &lt;a href=&quot;
